{{MusicRoom | category =[[Gensokyo]] | title =御伽の国の鬼が島 ～ {{lang|en|Missing Power}} | roma =Otogi no kuni no onigashima | titleEN =Onigashima in the Fairyland ~ Missing Power | composer =ZUN | comment = 伊吹萃香のテーマです。 子供に聞かせる御伽噺、桃太郎、一寸法師、そして金太郎などなど。 この曲はそんな御伽噺に出てくる、どこか楽しげで幸せそうだった鬼達をイメージしました。 この恐ろしくなさげがたまらないですよね。 さて、上の御伽噺の中に仲間外れが居るとしたら、一体どれだろう？ そんな事でも考えながら、今日も鬼とお酒でも飲みましょうか。 | translation = This is the theme of [[Suika Ibuki|Suika]]. There're plenty of fairy tales for children like [[wikipedia:Momotaro|Momotarou]], [[wikipedia:One-inch_boy|Issunboushi]], [[wikipedia:Kintaro|Kintarou]], etc. I wanted to make a song that would fit well with that sort of fun-loving, happy [[oni]]. That sort of fearlessness is irresistable. Anyway, there's a story that got left out of the ones I mentioned above; I wonder which it is? While we consider this, why don't we go drinking with an oni tonight, too? }}
{{MusicRoom | category =Ending Theme | title =夏明き | roma =Natsuaki | titleEN =End of Summer | composer =NKZ | comment = エンディングで流れる曲。 賑やかな祭りが終わった後は物悲しくなります。 夏冬の祭りはぐったりして気がつくと3日後ですが――。（後の祭り | translation = The music played at the ending scene. I can't help being a little sad after all the festivals end. During the summer and winter [[wikipedia:Comiket|Comiket]] festivals I'm totally exhausted, and before I know it all three days have passed... (Time for the festival afterwards.) }}
